text: Generated brief soil descriptions are created for major soil components.  The Zyme soil is a minor component.

The Awitava component makes up 85 percent of the map unit. Slopes are 3 to 9 percent. This component is on fan remnants. The parent material consists of eolian deposits over alluvium derived from diorite. Depth to a root restrictive layer is greater than 60 inches. The natural drainage class is well drained.  Water movement in the most restrictive layer is very low. Available water to a depth of 60 inches (or restricted depth) is very low. Shrink-swell potential is low. This soil is not flooded. It is not ponded. There is no zone of water saturation within a depth of 72 inches. Organic matter content in the surface horizon is about 2 percent. This component is in the R036XY113CO Semidesert Juniper Loam ecological site. Nonirrigated land capability classification is 6s.  This soil does not meet hydric criteria. The calcium carbonate equivalent within 40 inches, typically, does not exceed 60 percent. There are no saline horizons within 30 inches of the soil surface.
